 “If and else” are known as decision-making statements for our program.
 
 var1 =2
var2 =3
var3 = int(input())   #input integer tha usko typecast kia

if var3 > var2:    #if is a keyword thatswhy highlighted in pycharm
    print("var3 is greater")
if var3 == var2:  #: helps to enter print type kr k he print k agye space dedeta
    print("Equal")    
else:
    print("var2 is greater")
    
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
****************Output**********

4                               #if first IF condition is true it will check all remaing if in the program, to avoid that we use Elif
var3 is greater
var2 is greater             
_________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

