list = [1,3,4]
print(5 in list)
if 1 in list :          #in is a keyword
    print("Yes it's in list")   # this is printed as if condition is true ,agr if condition false hoti to nhi print nhi hota
    if 15 in list:
        print("Yes not in list")   #if condition false hai isliye print nhi hua

________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
********************Output**************************************

False
Yes it's in list
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Short Hand If Else Notation In Python
“An executable statement, written in so compact manner that it comprises of only a single line of code is known as shorthand statement.”

If-expression if(Condition) else else-expression     //Syntax
____________________________________________________________________________________________________
a= int(input("Enter the value of a \n"))
b= int(input("Enter the value of b \n"))

print("A is greater than B") if(a>b) else print("B is greater than A")
___________________________________________________________________________________________________
****************Output*******************

Enter the value of a 
2
Enter the value of b 
5
B is greater than A





